description:
PREDATORS contains stories based around the PREDATORY theme, be it from the perspective of the PREDATOR or the PREY.

Lions, Tigers, Bears, and more - Oh My! Stalk and be stalked in this suspenseful collection of tales of a predatory nature. Wild beasts, hunters, cave girls and subtle terrors all feature in 25 self contained strips in the latest instalment of Accent UK's quality themed anthology series. Featuring established and emerging creators from around the globe.
name: Predators

description: WESTERN is the 2009 anthology, with an excellent wrap around cover by Kirk Manley, given the Accent UK feel by Andy Bloor. This latest anthology maintaining the high standard set by ZOMBIES and ROBOTS sees a number of stories based around the theme of the old American West.
name: Western Anthology

description: A trade paperback collecting the thrilling 9-issue miniseries by acclaimed novelist Greg Rucka (Smoker, A Fistful of Rain) with art by Klaus Janson (BATMAN: THE DARK KNIGHT RETURNS)! A dying Ra's al Ghul has no choice but to beg Batman, his greatest nemesis, for help against a woman who once shared his life, centuries ago. In exchange, he offers the Dark Knight a chance of a lifetime - the ability to speak with his dead parents. But what Batman's parents have to say to him will profoundly affect both the man and the hero. This collection also includes an introduction by series editor Matt Idelson and behind-the-scenes unused pages and sketches featuring commentary by Janson. collection also includes an introduction by series editor Matt Idelson and behind-the-scenes unused pages and sketches featuring commentary by Janson.
name: Death and the Maidens TPB

description: Contains chapters 10-13 of Problem Sleuth, with author notes on each page.
name: Problem Sleuth: Suitor to the Sodajerk's Confidante

description: 4 kids decided to play a game, but it turns out there more to this complicated game than meets the eye, and the kids find themselves in some deep trouble trying to win a no-win scenario.
name: Homestuck Book 1
Die Höhle am Ende der Welt

description: X-23 thought she had walked away from her past, but after her brutal discoveries in Madripoor, she realizes there are some crimes - of the heart and body - that cannot be so easily forgotten. But as memories begin to spin her out of control, an old mentor and maybe a new enemy come back into her life: Wolverine...and the vampire, Jubilee. Collects X-23 #10-16.
name: Volume 2
